Reasoning: The paper presents linear time approximation schemes for generalized matching problems on nonbipartite graphs, which are fundamental problems in graph theory and combinatorial optimization. The techniques used in the paper involve maintaining relaxed complementary slackness and approximation-preserving reductions, which are common tools in the design and analysis of approximation algorithms. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics), cs.CG (Computational Geometry), cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory), and cs.CC (Computational Complexity).
